The [https://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Operating system operating system (OS)] is the main software system on your computer running all the programs that you want to run.

== Systems ==
OpenTTD currently runs in the following operating systems:
* AmigaOS <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.os4depot.net/index.php?function=showfile&file=game/strategy/openttd.lha]
* BeOS 5, Zeta 1.1 (x86 only) <strong>[*]</strong> [http://bebits.com/app/3810]
* FreeBSD [http://www.freebsdsoftware.org/games/openttd.html]
* Linux [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717] (NOTE: different Linux variations and distributions behave differently, but some of them include OpenTTD in their packaging system in up-to-date version)
* MacOS X (10.3.9 or newer) [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* MorphOS <strong>[*]</strong> [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* NetBSD [http://riksun.riken.go.jp/pub/pub/NetBSD/NetBSD-current/pkgsrc/games/openttd/]
* OpenBSD [http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/ports/games/openttd/]
* OS/2 [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]
* Palm OS 5 <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.esoftinteractive.com/openttd.html]
* ReactOS (runs the Windows binary) [http://reactosde.re.funpic.de/catappdetail.php?cat=Games&appnr=146]
* RiscOS [http://www.flypig.co.uk/?page=riscos&dnload=risc+os]
* SkyOS <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.tt-forums.net/viewtopic.php?t=8107]
* Solaris [http://www.softagalleria.net/openttd-solaris.php]
* Symbian S60v3 <strong>[*]</strong> [http://www.tt-forums.net/viewtopic.php?f=33&t=35942&st=0&sk=t&sd=a]
* Windows 95/98/ME/2000/NT/XP/Vista/7 [http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=103924&package_id=111717]

